title: The Churches of Mexico 1530-1810 (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
pdf / English / 324 pages / 1962 / University of California Press / 47.4 MB

The serious literature, in English, on viceregal or colonial Mexican religious architecture and art is not large. Since Sylvester Baxter's pioneer study of 1901 (Spanish-Colonial Architecture in Mexico), there have been only a few works which have attempted and achieved accuracy of fact, integrity of scholarship, and sensitivity to the special character of the viceroyalty of New Spain
